@startuml cascade-growth
' Incremental det/min state-count growth through the ASR cascade:
'   G ‚Üí L‚àòG ‚Üí det(L‚àòG) ‚Üí C‚àòdet(L‚àòG) ‚Üí det(C‚àòL‚àòG) ‚Üí H‚àò‚Ä¶ ‚Üí N
' Determinizing after each composition keeps the state count bounded instead of
' exploding. Stage labels mirror CascadeStats in src/asr/cascade.rs; the counts
' are the illustrative figures from docs/asr/cascade-construction.md.
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam ArrowColor #BF360C
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.4
skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 12
  FontColor #102027
  BorderColor #E65100
}

title <b>Cascade growth with incremental determinization</b>\n<size:11><latex>N = \pi( \min( \det( H \circ \det( C \circ \det( L \circ G ) ) ) ) )</latex>  ‚Äî  det/min cap the state count after each <latex>\circ</latex></size>

rectangle "<b>G</b> ‚Äî grammar\n<latex>\approx</latex> 1K states" as G #FFE0B2
rectangle "<b><latex>L \circ G</latex></b>\n<latex>\approx</latex> 500K states  (blow-up)" as LG #FFCC80
rectangle "<b><latex>\det(L \circ G)</latex></b>\n<latex>\approx</latex> 50K states  (<latex>10\times</latex> ‚Üì)" as DLG #FFE0B2
rectangle "<b><latex>C \circ \det(L \circ G)</latex></b>\n<latex>\approx</latex> 200K states" as CLG #FFCC80
rectangle "<b><latex>\det(C \circ L \circ G)</latex></b>\n<latex>\approx</latex> 100K states" as DCLG #FFE0B2
rectangle "<b><latex>H \circ \det(C \circ L \circ G)</latex></b>\nexpand HMM states" as HCLG #FFCC80
rectangle "<b>N</b> = <latex>\pi(\min(\dots))</latex>\nminimal decoding graph" as N #FFB74D

G   -right-> LG   : <latex>\circ</latex> L
LG  -right-> DLG  : det
DLG -right-> CLG  : <latex>\circ</latex> C
CLG -right-> DCLG : det
DCLG -right-> HCLG : <latex>\circ</latex> H
HCLG -right-> N    : min ¬∑ <latex>\pi</latex>

note bottom of LG
  Without incremental det the <latex>L \circ G</latex> product can reach
  millions of states and exhaust memory before C and H
  are even composed (docs/asr/cascade-construction.md).
end note

note bottom of DCLG
  After each composition, <b>det</b> (powerset construction)
  removes redundant paths and <latex>\varepsilon</latex>-arcs; the final <b>min</b>
  merges equivalent states; <b><latex>\pi</latex></b> erases auxiliary symbols.
end note
@enduml
